        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> cfallin submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13615#pullrequestreview-4481120806\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 602316508,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781218037
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13615#discussion_r3399615973\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For all of these cases where we have a region specifically for an offset in vmctx, then we load from that offset, perhaps it would make sense to bundle together into a helper <code>func_env.load_from_vmctx_offset(...)</code> or somesuch so that we know it's correct (no copy/paste errors or whatever)?</p>\n</blockquote>",
